---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Services — Cody Smith" description="Web management, marketing strategy, training, and AI workflow advisory.">
  <section class="pt-32 pb-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-amber-500 font-mono text-sm tracking-wider mb-6">Services</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-stone-100 leading-tight mb-8">
        What I do and<br />how it's structured.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-stone-400 text-lg leading-relaxed">
        Everything runs on monthly retainers. No hourly billing surprises, no vague scopes. Each service has clear tiers — you pick the level of involvement that fits.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Web Management -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 border-t border-stone-800/50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="mb-10">
        <span class="text-amber-500 font-mono text-xs tracking-wider">01</span>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-stone-100 mt-2">Web Management</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-500 mt-1 text-sm italic">Keep it running.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="text-stone-400 leading-relaxed space-y-4 mb-10">
        <p>
          Your website is infrastructure. It needs hosting that isn't shared with a thousand other sites, security monitoring that catches problems before your customers do, and someone who actually reads the update logs before clicking "update all."
        </p>
        <p>
          I manage WordPress sites on dedicated cloud hosting. Monthly site health reports show you exactly what happened, what's next, and what to watch. You never wonder if the work is getting done.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
        <div class="p-4 border border-stone-800/50 rounded">
          <p class="text-stone-500 mb-2">Includes</p>
          <ul class="text-stone-400 space-y-1">
            <li>Managed cloud hosting</li>
            <li>Security monitoring & SSL</li>
            <li>Core, theme, and plugin updates</li>
            <li>Daily backups</li>
            <li>Uptime monitoring</li>
            <li>Monthly Site Health Report</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 border border-stone-800/50 rounded">
          <p class="text-stone-500 mb-2">Priced by</p>
          <p class="text-stone-400">Site complexity (pages, integrations, traffic). Tiered — pick the hours and reporting level you need. Multi-site discounts available.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Marketing Strategy -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 border-t border-stone-800/50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="mb-10">
        <span class="text-amber-500 font-mono text-xs tracking-wider">02</span>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-stone-100 mt-2">Marketing Strategy</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-500 mt-1 text-sm italic">Decisions and priorities.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="text-stone-400 leading-relaxed space-y-4 mb-10">
        <p>
          Strategy means telling you what to do, in what order, and why it matters more than the other twelve things competing for your attention. It means an SEO roadmap built on real keyword data, not guesswork. Competitive analysis that names names. Content briefs your writer can actually use.
        </p>
        <p>
          I don't execute the marketing — I direct it. You get the plan, the priorities, and the reasoning. Monthly calls keep it on track. Quarterly reviews adjust the course.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
        <div class="p-4 border border-stone-800/50 rounded">
          <p class="text-stone-500 mb-2">Includes</p>
          <ul class="text-stone-400 space-y-1">
            <li>Comprehensive site & SEO audit</li>
            <li>Keyword research & strategy</li>
            <li>Competitive analysis</li>
            <li>Content briefs & direction</li>
            <li>Monthly strategy calls</li>
            <li>Quarterly reporting</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 border border-stone-800/50 rounded">
          <p class="text-stone-500 mb-2">Starts with</p>
          <p class="text-stone-400">A strategic audit — a full read of your site, your market, and your competitors. The audit findings become your roadmap. Everything after that is execution and refinement.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Implementation -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 border-t border-stone-800/50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="mb-10">
        <span class="text-amber-500 font-mono text-xs tracking-wider">03</span>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-stone-100 mt-2">Implementation</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-500 mt-1 text-sm italic">Changes to production systems.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="text-stone-400 leading-relaxed space-y-4 mb-10">
        <p>
          Some work doesn't fit a retainer. Site migrations, CRM integrations, analytics setup, landing page builds — these are projects with a start, a scope, and a finish line.
        </p>
        <p>
          I scope it, quote it, build it, and hand it over. No ambiguity about what's included.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-sm">
        <div class="p-4 border border-stone-800/50 rounded">
          <p class="text-stone-300 font-medium mb-1">Migrations</p>
          <p class="text-stone-500">Host, DNS, email, plugins — moved without downtime.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 border border-stone-800/50 rounded">
          <p class="text-stone-300 font-medium mb-1">Integrations</p>
          <p class="text-stone-500">Form-to-CRM, analytics, email marketing, payment.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 border border-stone-800/50 rounded">
          <p class="text-stone-300 font-medium mb-1">Page Builds</p>
          <p class="text-stone-500">Landing pages, service pages, content rewrites.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Training -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 border-t border-stone-800/50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="mb-10">
        <span class="text-amber-500 font-mono text-xs tracking-wider">04</span>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-stone-100 mt-2">Training</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-500 mt-1 text-sm italic">Changes capability.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="text-stone-400 leading-relaxed space-y-4 mb-10">
        <p>
          Training that works doesn't happen in a single afternoon webinar. It's a guided program — three sessions over three to four weeks, with real assignments between them. Your team practices on their own systems, makes real mistakes in a safe context, and builds actual skill.
        </p>
        <p>
          I design training using the same learning science frameworks used in professional instructional design — not because it sounds impressive, but because it's the difference between a team that attended training and a team that can do the work.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
        <div class="p-4 border border-stone-800/50 rounded">
          <p class="text-stone-300 font-medium mb-1">WordPress & SEO</p>
          <p class="text-stone-500">Content management, basic SEO, site maintenance — so your team can handle the daily work confidently.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 border border-stone-800/50 rounded">
          <p class="text-stone-300 font-medium mb-1">AI Workflows</p>
          <p class="text-stone-500">Practical AI integration for your existing processes. Not hype — judgment. When to use it, when not to, and how to tell the difference.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-20 px-6 border-t border-stone-800/50">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-100 mb-4">Want to talk specifics?</h2>
      <p class="text-stone-400 mb-8">Every engagement starts with a conversation about what you actually need — not a sales pitch.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 bg-amber-600 text-stone-950 font-medium text-sm rounded hover:bg-amber-500 transition-colors">
        Start a conversation
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
